1
00:02:21,116 --> 00:02:24,342
Stop, Yash. Stop.

2
00:02:45,984 --> 00:02:49,456
Pranab-da's dog bit Mr Vajpayee.

3
00:02:50,596 --> 00:02:53,658
Our Pranab-da? Pranab Mukherjee?

4
00:02:53,846 --> 00:02:55,689
A dog bit him on his walk.

5
00:02:55,926 --> 00:02:58,114
Oh no! Now that's 14 injections.

6
00:02:58,234 --> 00:02:59,536
That's not written here.

7
00:02:59,742 --> 00:03:02,453
He has no choice. What is it?

8
00:03:02,573 --> 00:03:04,832
- There's eggplant on the pen.
- So?

9
00:03:05,004 --> 00:03:06,974
I told you not to come
at lunchtime.

10
00:03:07,094 --> 00:03:10,084
Eggplant! It's not poison, is it?

11
00:03:10,992 --> 00:03:11,602
Strange fellow.

12
00:03:11,774 --> 00:03:14,545
- Who eats eggplant every day?
- Well, I do.

13
00:03:14,665 --> 00:03:16,126
Every day?

14
00:03:16,246 --> 00:03:17,525
I like it.

15
00:03:17,645 --> 00:03:18,919
Careful.

16
00:03:20,071 --> 00:03:21,103
What's this?

17
00:03:23,368 --> 00:03:24,705
- Well?
- An invitation.

18
00:03:24,825 --> 00:03:26,662
- To what?
- The World Cup.

19
00:03:26,995 --> 00:03:28,106
Really?

20
00:03:28,824 --> 00:03:31,100
The dacoit Phoolan Devi
is surrendering.

21
00:03:31,276 --> 00:03:34,003
- I hear she's beautiful.
- There's no photo.

22
00:03:34,587 --> 00:03:37,426
Look! The launch of the Maruti car.

23
00:03:46,801 --> 00:03:49,024
Kapil Dev, Mohinder Amarnath,

24
00:03:49,425 --> 00:03:52,993
Madan Lal, Kirti Azad,
Sunil Valson.

25
00:03:53,482 --> 00:03:55,895
Why are you taking their
bags with you, Mr Singh?

26
00:03:56,323 --> 00:03:59,773
Because they're already in England,
playing County Cricket.

27
00:03:59,893 --> 00:04:00,893
Congrats.

28
00:04:01,055 --> 00:04:03,347
You mean they've replaced Gavaskar
with this guy as captain?

29
00:04:03,371 --> 00:04:04,061
Hey!

30
00:04:04,225 --> 00:04:05,495
- Can he do it?
- Sure, he can.

31
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:06,953
That also in England?

32
00:04:07,254 --> 00:04:08,838
He can't even speak
English properly.

33
00:04:10,753 --> 00:04:12,192
But he plays cricket well.

34
00:04:12,478 --> 00:04:13,478
So what?

35
00:04:14,786 --> 00:04:16,535
When are you back, Mr Singh?

36
00:04:16,655 --> 00:04:18,705
When there are no more
matches for us to play.

37
00:04:19,002 --> 00:04:21,800
The East Africans aren't playing.
So, who will you defeat?

38
00:04:22,542 --> 00:04:25,736
The Cricket Board isn't even
hosting a farewell party.

39
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,480
Good luck!
Take care. See you.

40
00:04:28,711 --> 00:04:30,450
We'll celebrate when we're back.

41
00:04:30,911 --> 00:04:32,116
Celebrate what?

42
00:04:35,335 --> 00:04:36,743
Good luck, Mr Singh.

43
00:04:37,213 --> 00:04:38,679
All the best.

44
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:14,770
Well bowled, Kaps!

45
00:05:14,859 --> 00:05:18,221
Mr Dev, your call to India
is connected, sir.

46
00:05:20,877 --> 00:05:21,877
Hello, Romi.

47
00:05:22,028 --> 00:05:26,421
Romi's out right now, Kuku.
Talk to me instead.

48
00:05:27,543 --> 00:05:28,906
What will be happening here?

49
00:05:29,086 --> 00:05:31,950
Half the kids are drinking milk.
The others are playing cricket.

50
00:05:32,227 --> 00:05:35,725
You should play cricket all day
and drink gallons of milk.

51
00:05:35,845 --> 00:05:37,881
A call from London?
And you didn't tell me?

52
00:05:38,352 --> 00:05:41,681
Pinky, Happi, Guddo! Come,
a call from London.

53
00:05:41,881 --> 00:05:44,094
And you... Meshi!
Call Kake too.

54
00:05:44,293 --> 00:05:45,469
Come here!

55
00:05:45,589 --> 00:05:47,652
Give me the phone.

56
00:05:48,878 --> 00:05:50,526
Hello, Kuku!

57
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,800
Yes, Mama.

58
00:05:51,841 --> 00:05:54,502
- Are you wearing your sweater?
- <i>Yes, Mama. I will.</i>

59
00:05:54,837 --> 00:05:58,103
Son, win the Cup and come home.

60
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,491
Yes, Mama.

61
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:02,987
Tell me.

62
00:06:03,198 --> 00:06:04,200
Hello.

63
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,574
Hello.

64
00:06:05,694 --> 00:06:06,482
Hello.

65
00:06:06,602 --> 00:06:07,978
Hello.

66
00:06:12,815 --> 00:06:14,561
The line's cut.

67
00:06:14,855 --> 00:06:17,355
I didn't get a chance to talk.

68
00:06:21,307 --> 00:06:22,501
Kaps, catch!

69
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,506
Impossible!

70
00:06:24,626 --> 00:06:27,962
If Kapil catches it, I'll do
anything he wants me to.

71
00:06:30,364 --> 00:06:33,970
- Sorry, sorry. That was tough.
- Jimmy said,

72
00:06:34,090 --> 00:06:37,174
if you catch it, you can ask
for anything.

73
00:06:37,473 --> 00:06:40,771
I'll ask him to teach me English
before the World Cup starts.

74
00:06:40,891 --> 00:06:44,316
Asking for my life
would be easier!

75
00:06:44,964 --> 00:06:47,441
That reminds me.
Did you talk to Lala-ji today?

76
00:06:47,621 --> 00:06:50,880
- I'll do it now. Hold this.
- Give him my regards.

77
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,203
He isn't scared of the world's
fastest bowlers,

78
00:06:53,456 --> 00:06:55,698
but trembles when he hears
Lala-ji's name.

79
00:06:56,422 --> 00:07:00,166
Lala-ji, they're not playing
proper cricket.

80
00:07:00,286 --> 00:07:02,858
60 overs. Start in the morning
finish in the evening.

81
00:07:03,051 --> 00:07:06,029
Carry on like this and the game
will be reduced to 10 or 20 overs.

82
00:07:06,149 --> 00:07:08,310
Sharma-ji, what nonsense!

83
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:11,260
- Mr Jimmy is on the line.
- He'll live a hundred years.

84
00:07:11,603 --> 00:07:14,835
Hello, Jimmy, my son.
How are you?

85
00:07:15,071 --> 00:07:18,739
<i>I'm sending you two bottles
of pickle with Yash.</i>

86
00:07:19,846 --> 00:07:22,607
Mr Singh, why do you have
so many bottles of pickle?

87
00:07:23,124 --> 00:07:25,044
Opening a store in London?

88
00:07:25,164 --> 00:07:28,297
The food's so bland there.

89
00:07:28,504 --> 00:07:31,082
Can't eat without pickles.

90
00:07:31,202 --> 00:07:34,648
Well, sir, you'll have to pay
excess baggage.

91
00:07:34,828 --> 00:07:36,889
Or leave some behind.

92
00:07:38,178 --> 00:07:39,882
Give me a receipt.

93
00:07:42,290 --> 00:07:43,672
Maan, we're vegetarians.

94
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:45,710
How will we eat there?

95
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:48,132
That's 5800-rupees.

96
00:07:48,293 --> 00:07:50,512
But, sir, I don't have
that much on me.

97
00:07:50,994 --> 00:07:52,457
Here.

98
00:07:52,577 --> 00:07:55,446
Ask your office to pay
the money tomorrow.

99
00:07:56,015 --> 00:07:57,158
Yes.

100
00:07:57,889 --> 00:08:00,559
Mr Singh! Will you do me a favour?

101
00:08:00,755 --> 00:08:03,425
- Can you get me an autograph?
- You can ask them now.

102
00:08:04,256 --> 00:08:05,256
No, no.

103
00:08:05,542 --> 00:08:06,789
I mean Viv Richards.

104
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:09,108
Please try.

105
00:08:09,816 --> 00:08:11,110
Don't forget.

106
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:12,860
Thank you very much.

107
00:08:14,253 --> 00:08:18,129
I'll get you Queen Elizabeth's
autograph too. You fool!

108
00:08:19,414 --> 00:08:20,845
Sunil Gavaskar.

109
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:25,180
Syed Kirmani.

110
00:08:27,629 --> 00:08:29,010
Yashpal Sharma.

111
00:08:31,751 --> 00:08:33,806
Krishnamachari Srikkanth.

112
00:08:34,748 --> 00:08:36,491
Dilip Vengsarkar.

113
00:08:37,876 --> 00:08:39,483
Roger Binny.

114
00:08:40,423 --> 00:08:42,167
Balwinder Singh Sandhu.

115
00:08:43,675 --> 00:08:45,081
Sandeep Patil.

116
00:08:46,328 --> 00:08:48,002
Ravi Shastri.

117
00:08:49,069 --> 00:08:51,311
PR Man Singh.

118
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,422
Where's our team bus?

119
00:09:29,633 --> 00:09:32,492
No, no. No bus here
for Indian team.

120
00:09:38,951 --> 00:09:42,119
You mean on flight only?
When?

121
00:09:43,462 --> 00:09:46,499
Rascal! You just got engaged.

122
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:48,629
Not for you.

123
00:09:48,837 --> 00:09:50,635
The bus is here.

124
00:09:52,369 --> 00:09:54,548
- Tell me more.
- Let's get on the bus.

125
00:09:55,614 --> 00:10:00,433
- Did something happen?
- None of your business.

126
00:10:01,975 --> 00:10:03,558
Tell me!

127
00:10:03,678 --> 00:10:05,238
Patla told the airhostess
on our flight:

128
00:10:05,425 --> 00:10:06,957
"Hi, I'm Sandeep Patil.

129
00:10:07,077 --> 00:10:08,180
Sandy to you."

130
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:10,407
Then Yashpal says,

131
00:10:10,602 --> 00:10:12,409
"Hi, I'm Yash to you."

132
00:10:13,061 --> 00:10:15,684
The rascal added if India wins
the World Cup,

133
00:10:16,138 --> 00:10:17,794
he'll eat this newspaper.

134
00:10:18,657 --> 00:10:22,088
Ballu was next. And you know
what he said?

135
00:10:22,402 --> 00:10:25,738
He says to her:
"Hi, I'm Balwinder Singh Sandhu."

136
00:10:26,278 --> 00:10:27,880
"Balls to you!"

137
00:10:28,903 --> 00:10:30,276
Listen, everyone.

138
00:10:31,072 --> 00:10:32,936
Listen, everyone.

139
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:39,201
Today for the vegetarians, there's
only bread, butter and salad.

140
00:10:40,129 --> 00:10:41,778
Why look at me, Cheeka?

141
00:10:41,898 --> 00:10:44,248
- We'll sort it out tomorrow.
- Listen, soldiers!

142
00:10:44,921 --> 00:10:47,539
Welcome to London!

143
00:10:49,973 --> 00:10:53,153
We must play four warm-up matches
before the tournament.

144
00:10:54,611 --> 00:10:55,971
Let's show them what
we're made of.

145
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:04,200
<i>This moment is frozen in time</i>

146
00:11:11,975 --> 00:11:14,250
<i>A glorious dream is a few steps away</i>

147
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:16,579
- What?
- South Indian.

148
00:11:25,989 --> 00:11:28,109
What's this rubbish you're eating?
Five, ten, fifteen.

149
00:11:33,172 --> 00:11:39,070
<i>Today belongs to you.</i>

150
00:11:43,094 --> 00:11:44,803
Go outside.

151
00:11:46,892 --> 00:11:48,160
Hello, Simran.

152
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,774
- Did you get there safely?
- Yes, I'm in London.

153
00:11:50,976 --> 00:11:53,658
- Have you eaten?
- Yes, I have.

154
00:11:53,824 --> 00:11:55,469
The airhostess served us lunch.
Very nice.

155
00:11:55,589 --> 00:11:57,438
"Nice?" The airhostess?

156
00:11:57,558 --> 00:11:59,037
No, the food was nice.

157
00:11:59,829 --> 00:12:03,133
<i>Cross the bumpy roads ahead</i>

158
00:12:03,253 --> 00:12:04,830
Good ball, Kaps.

159
00:12:06,425 --> 00:12:08,288
What a shot! It's a boundary, bro.

160
00:12:09,536 --> 00:12:11,052
Inswinger.

161
00:12:14,196 --> 00:12:16,138
Easy, Cheeka.
It's only net practice.

162
00:12:16,258 --> 00:12:17,641
When I hit, I hit hard.

163
00:12:18,338 --> 00:12:20,344
I don't know how to play defence.

164
00:12:20,464 --> 00:12:23,063
I know only hitting.
Go, go bowl.

165
00:12:24,003 --> 00:12:25,811
Kapil, I'll end up hitting his head.

166
00:12:25,931 --> 00:12:28,720
He doesn't know defence.

167
00:12:29,323 --> 00:12:31,619
Mr Man Singh, how may I help you?

168
00:12:32,394 --> 00:12:36,336
This pass says entry to all
stadiums except Lord's.

169
00:12:36,653 --> 00:12:39,006
But India doesn't have any game
at Lord's.

170
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:42,419
But the Finals are at Lord's,
right?

171
00:12:43,534 --> 00:12:48,406
So Mr Man Singh, if and when
India reaches the Final,

172
00:12:48,773 --> 00:12:50,354
we shall happily issue you the pass.

173
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:52,056
OK.

174
00:13:03,689 --> 00:13:04,956
Inswinger.

175
00:13:06,613 --> 00:13:11,248
When you bowl an inswinger,
must you telegram the batsman?

176
00:13:12,211 --> 00:13:15,405
Hide your grip.
Come on! Again.

177
00:13:30,626 --> 00:13:31,888
That's good.

178
00:13:32,919 --> 00:13:34,690
Where were you, brother?

179
00:13:36,063 --> 00:13:39,195
- Learning a lesson.
- What lesson?

180
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:42,932
Just that we may have gained
our independence 35 years ago,

181
00:13:45,573 --> 00:13:48,139
but we haven't yet won respect,
Captain.

182
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:04,099
Ballu.

183
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:15,481
A girl? In Ballu's room?

184
00:14:15,601 --> 00:14:19,399
Yes! She must've just showered
because her hair was wet.

185
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:23,479
- And Ballu?
- Must have been in the shower?

186
00:14:25,156 --> 00:14:25,962
Why weren't they bathing together?

187
00:14:26,082 --> 00:14:27,082
I'll find out.

188
00:14:27,144 --> 00:14:28,744
Do you plan to rub their backs
with soap?

189
00:14:30,094 --> 00:14:32,506
No! It can't be Ballu.

190
00:14:32,785 --> 00:14:34,351
It just can't be him.

191
00:14:34,517 --> 00:14:37,279
He just got engaged to Simran.

192
00:14:37,473 --> 00:14:39,261
There was a girl near the nets.

193
00:14:39,864 --> 00:14:41,624
Maybe it was her.

194
00:14:45,145 --> 00:14:46,689
Kaps...

195
00:14:49,605 --> 00:14:51,149
Thank you, Kaps.

196
00:14:59,807 --> 00:15:01,296
What is it?

197
00:15:14,485 --> 00:15:15,610
Catch!

198
00:15:38,727 --> 00:15:40,879
<i>Another wicket down for India.</i>

199
00:15:40,999 --> 00:15:42,733
<i>They're looking in trouble here.</i>

200
00:15:42,853 --> 00:15:45,009
Just 82 for 5.

201
00:15:45,224 --> 00:15:48,054
Not a very good start to
their World Cup preparations.

202
00:15:48,174 --> 00:15:49,693
The team is hopeless.

203
00:15:49,813 --> 00:15:52,012
Don't lose face here.

204
00:15:52,132 --> 00:15:54,336
We'll be disgraced.

205
00:15:54,558 --> 00:15:57,546
At least win one match. Just one.

206
00:15:59,316 --> 00:16:01,556
Kapil Dev!

207
00:16:01,781 --> 00:16:03,571
Kapil Dev!

208
00:16:03,691 --> 00:16:05,853
Autograph, please.

209
00:16:12,208 --> 00:16:14,844
I'm a fast bowler too.

210
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:17,716
- Do you drink milk too?
- Yes.

211
00:16:17,836 --> 00:16:20,643
If you come to watch the match,
then cheer loudly.

212
00:16:21,673 --> 00:16:23,731
But I can't come.

213
00:16:23,956 --> 00:16:27,138
Because Papa says India never wins,

214
00:16:27,258 --> 00:16:29,996
so why waste precious money
on tickets.

215
00:16:39,353 --> 00:16:41,698
Kapil, in the run up
to the World Cup,

216
00:16:41,818 --> 00:16:43,719
your team has lost
3 practice matches.

217
00:16:43,839 --> 00:16:46,936
One against a minor county.

218
00:16:48,181 --> 00:16:49,842
You talk...

219
00:16:50,673 --> 00:16:53,226
You talk like fast bowler.

220
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:57,611
Can you talk slow like spin bowler?

221
00:16:58,288 --> 00:17:00,701
My hand little tight in English.

222
00:17:00,926 --> 00:17:05,856
What do you think your team's
chances are in the World Cup?

223
00:17:07,541 --> 00:17:09,911
We here to win!

224
00:17:11,571 --> 00:17:13,456
To win the World Cup?

225
00:17:15,229 --> 00:17:17,832
What else we here for?

226
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:27,185
In the history of the World Cup,

227
00:17:27,305 --> 00:17:29,443
the West Indies haven't lost
a match.

228
00:17:30,104 --> 00:17:31,716
Not one!

229
00:17:31,930 --> 00:17:33,273
Michael Holding.

230
00:17:33,393 --> 00:17:35,196
He's known as "Whispering Death."

231
00:17:38,357 --> 00:17:41,492
It's like a bullet,
if it hits you

232
00:17:41,776 --> 00:17:43,527
you're dead.

233
00:17:45,285 --> 00:17:46,980
That's Andy Roberts.

234
00:17:47,437 --> 00:17:49,305
He's called the "Hitman".

235
00:17:50,565 --> 00:17:52,779
He kills them one by one.

236
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:06,075
Kapil, tomorrow you're meeting the
Queen at Buckingham Palace.

237
00:18:06,195 --> 00:18:07,538
What will you say to her?

238
00:18:08,187 --> 00:18:12,903
I'll get her blessings, so
we will win the World Cup.

239
00:18:14,794 --> 00:18:16,544
And that's Marshall.

240
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:19,859
The shortest, but the fastest.

241
00:18:25,383 --> 00:18:29,156
And there's Big Bird.
Joel Garner.

242
00:18:31,624 --> 00:18:33,568
He's 6ft 8".

243
00:18:33,688 --> 00:18:37,780
His outstretched hand is 3ft,
then he jumps 2ft,

244
00:18:38,005 --> 00:18:40,410
so his ball comes at you
from a height of 12 feet.

245
00:18:40,626 --> 00:18:44,146
And at 150kms per hour.
Time to run for cover!

246
00:18:44,266 --> 00:18:45,625
Shut up!

247
00:18:46,081 --> 00:18:48,234
Is this cricket or a horror film?

248
00:18:48,406 --> 00:18:49,906
Why scare everyone?

249
00:18:52,219 --> 00:18:53,650
No, no. Sir, no!

250
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:56,686
Kapil was just being enthusiastic.

251
00:18:56,862 --> 00:18:59,361
Our return is confirmed for June 20th,

252
00:18:59,481 --> 00:19:01,078
before the semi-finals.

253
00:19:01,264 --> 00:19:03,354
<i>Talk later. I'm off to
Buckingham Palace.</i>

254
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:05,403
<i>There's a protocol meeting.</i>

255
00:19:05,785 --> 00:19:08,295
Once the Queen approaches
the players,

256
00:19:08,415 --> 00:19:10,649
she will extend her hand out
to them.

257
00:19:10,769 --> 00:19:15,909
They must hold the tip
of her fingers gently,

258
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:18,160
and make a small bow
from the neck.

259
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:20,214
Like this.

260
00:19:20,695 --> 00:19:22,887
The team will then proceed to Lord's

