00:34:43,221 --> 00:34:45,684
<i>Richards is making this look too easy.</i>

506
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,516
Rain, gentlemen.

507
00:35:00,186 --> 00:35:04,177
Ballu, tell him you'll deal
with him tomorrow.

508
00:35:04,758 --> 00:35:06,728
Drop it! Why make trouble?

509
00:35:06,848 --> 00:35:07,885
Tell him.

510
00:35:08,005 --> 00:35:10,392
He won't forget it when he faces
your bowling.

511
00:35:10,619 --> 00:35:12,045
He'll be shit scared.

512
00:35:12,165 --> 00:35:14,502
Scared? Madipaa, he's Viv Richards!

513
00:35:14,749 --> 00:35:15,749
He whacks so hard.

514
00:35:15,803 --> 00:35:16,967
Even the ball gets terrified.

515
00:35:17,087 --> 00:35:20,594
- Scared? As if!
- So what if he's Viv Richards?

516
00:35:20,776 --> 00:35:22,614
Remember what Kaps said?

517
00:35:22,734 --> 00:35:24,579
Don't be scared. Just tell him.

518
00:35:26,195 --> 00:35:27,757
Go on!

519
00:35:28,573 --> 00:35:29,957
Hey, listen.

520
00:35:32,310 --> 00:35:33,310
What do I say?

521
00:35:33,349 --> 00:35:34,939
"I'll deal with you tomorrow."

522
00:35:36,096 --> 00:35:37,468
See you tomorrow!

523
00:35:38,067 --> 00:35:39,550
Yeah, man.

524
00:35:42,413 --> 00:35:44,743
- You're mine.
- Careful what you ask for, man.

525
00:35:46,576 --> 00:35:47,726
Now drop it!

526
00:35:47,846 --> 00:35:48,699
Want to sing him a lullaby?

527
00:35:48,819 --> 00:35:50,105
<i>Well, that's what you call luck.</i>

528
00:35:50,269 --> 00:35:51,523
<i>Saved by the rain.</i>

529
00:35:51,643 --> 00:35:53,861
<i>It looked like Viv Richards
was single-handedly</i>

530
00:35:53,981 --> 00:35:56,177
<i>going to take that game away
from the Indians.</i>

531
00:35:56,598 --> 00:35:58,512
The game resumes tomorrow.

532
00:35:58,994 --> 00:36:00,294
Let's see what happens.

533
00:36:05,322 --> 00:36:07,165
The match is starting.

534
00:36:11,307 --> 00:36:13,221
<i>Second day of play.
Richards on strike</i>

535
00:36:13,341 --> 00:36:15,884
<i>and Roger Binny to begin
India's bowling attack.</i>

536
00:36:16,117 --> 00:36:18,259
<i>Let's see what Viv does today.</i>

537
00:36:21,474 --> 00:36:24,061
<i>Binny running in on this overcast day.</i>

538
00:36:24,718 --> 00:36:27,117
<i>Kirmani catches it and
Viv Richards is out for 17.</i>

539
00:36:29,287 --> 00:36:31,661
<i>Richards is back in the pavilion.</i>

540
00:36:31,781 --> 00:36:33,830
Didn't I tell you, Ballu?

541
00:36:43,456 --> 00:36:45,459
Hey, you!

542
00:36:45,664 --> 00:36:46,944
Get back to work.

543
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:48,564
You had the day off yesterday!

544
00:36:48,684 --> 00:36:50,025
Go on.

545
00:36:51,039 --> 00:36:52,899
<i>Madan Lal bowls out Bacchus.</i>

546
00:36:53,019 --> 00:36:54,502
<i>What a brilliant delivery!</i>

547
00:36:55,021 --> 00:36:58,315
<i>Binny to Dujon and he's caught
by Sandhu.</i>

548
00:36:58,435 --> 00:37:01,254
<i>West Indies struggling at 107/5.</i>

549
00:37:02,241 --> 00:37:03,658
<i>Shastri to Gomes.</i>

550
00:37:04,858 --> 00:37:06,536
<i>Batsman are going for the second.</i>

551
00:37:06,656 --> 00:37:07,656
<i>Sandhu gets the ball.</i>

552
00:37:07,771 --> 00:37:09,391
<i>And that's a brilliant run out.</i>

553
00:37:10,099 --> 00:37:11,587
<i>This is unbelievable.</i>

554
00:37:11,755 --> 00:37:13,583
<i>The mighty West Indies are crumbling.</i>

555
00:37:20,398 --> 00:37:24,949
<i>The champions are
in trouble at 157/9.</i>

556
00:37:25,461 --> 00:37:27,419
Big Bird Joel Garner is the last man in,

557
00:37:27,539 --> 00:37:29,474
but 106 runs are still needed to win.

558
00:37:32,048 --> 00:37:34,774
<i>That's a big 6 over mid-wicket.</i>

559
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,796
<i>This is the same Andy Roberts who, in 1975,</i>

560
00:37:38,977 --> 00:37:41,066
<i>together with Deryck Murray</i>

561
00:37:41,186 --> 00:37:44,013
<i>added 64 runs for a 10th wicket
partnership.</i>

562
00:37:44,201 --> 00:37:45,834
<i>They made their team win.</i>

563
00:37:46,211 --> 00:37:49,040
<i>Looks like Andy Roberts
and Joel Garner</i>

564
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:51,651
<i>intend to perform the
same miracle today.</i>

565
00:37:51,771 --> 00:37:54,917
<i>The West Indies need only
34 runs to win.</i>

566
00:37:55,622 --> 00:37:58,815
Kaps, get Shastri back.

567
00:38:01,030 --> 00:38:02,646
They can't play slow spin.

568
00:38:05,442 --> 00:38:06,954
<i>Shastri has been called back.</i>

569
00:38:07,074 --> 00:38:09,008
<i>That could be a big risk.</i>

570
00:38:09,307 --> 00:38:10,564
<i>The game is at a crucial point.</i>

571
00:38:10,684 --> 00:38:13,431
<i>The West Indies need 34 runs
off 36 balls.</i>

572
00:38:18,617 --> 00:38:21,158
<i>India has done the unthinkable.</i>

573
00:38:21,278 --> 00:38:23,155
They've defeated the unbeatable.

574
00:38:23,275 --> 00:38:26,177
The invincible West Indies!

575
00:38:33,334 --> 00:38:38,387
<i>I was away working for 12 years.</i>

576
00:38:41,359 --> 00:38:45,513
<i>I returned with a ring.</i>

577
00:38:51,033 --> 00:38:53,430
<i>India has won!</i>

578
00:38:54,105 --> 00:38:59,219
<i>It's time to dance and sing.</i>

579
00:39:25,498 --> 00:39:28,915
Will Kaps get angry with us?
Tomorrow we're playing a match.

580
00:39:29,498 --> 00:39:31,207
How will he find out?

581
00:39:31,332 --> 00:39:33,335
He must've had his milk
and gone to sleep.

582
00:39:35,539 --> 00:39:36,978
Let's go!

583
00:39:39,919 --> 00:39:42,088
Tomorrow's a match day.

584
00:39:44,636 --> 00:39:46,051
Fix your hair.

585
00:39:49,290 --> 00:39:50,682
Where to, gang?

586
00:39:50,952 --> 00:39:54,361
We've won the first World Cup match.
Why not celebrate?

587
00:39:54,582 --> 00:39:56,457
- You coming?
- No, sir.

588
00:39:56,721 --> 00:39:59,883
I'm captain in the day.
Patla is the night Captain.

589
00:40:01,332 --> 00:40:04,498
They aren't as experienced
as you are on fast pitches.

590
00:40:05,543 --> 00:40:06,981
Put your helmet on.

591
00:40:12,568 --> 00:40:16,540
If I see someone yawning tomorrow,
they've had it.

592
00:40:16,665 --> 00:40:19,290
Kirti, you trouble-maker!

593
00:40:20,082 --> 00:40:22,582
Where are you going, Kaps?

594
00:40:23,498 --> 00:40:26,540
The ball has stained my trousers.
It look bad.

595
00:40:26,749 --> 00:40:29,665
- I'm taking it to the laundry.
- Has your family sent you money?

596
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:34,415
We get only £15 a day.

597
00:40:35,004 --> 00:40:37,183
Laundry will cost you about £12.

598
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:40,415
Buy a new pair of trousers
instead.

599
00:40:40,832 --> 00:40:43,107
- So?
- Wash them yourself.

600
00:40:44,915 --> 00:40:48,415
I haven't even washed a hanky
in my life.

601
00:40:48,540 --> 00:40:53,150
Nor have you wiped out the
West Indies team!

602
00:40:54,188 --> 00:40:56,503
There's a first for everything.

603
00:40:56,623 --> 00:41:00,087
<i>Being young is a carefree time</i>

604
00:41:00,207 --> 00:41:03,888
<i>We're ready to falter and fall</i>

605
00:41:04,207 --> 00:41:07,165
<i>This no age anyway</i>

606
00:41:07,290 --> 00:41:09,786
<i>To be all grown up</i>

607
00:41:11,498 --> 00:41:15,082
<i>Crazy thoughts flood all our hearts</i>

608
00:41:15,207 --> 00:41:19,045
<i>Let's cross all boundaries</i>

609
00:41:19,165 --> 00:41:22,082
<i>This no age anyway</i>

610
00:41:22,202 --> 00:41:24,848
<i>To be all grown up</i>

611
00:41:29,559 --> 00:41:31,540
Jimpa, I managed it in £1.

612
00:41:31,660 --> 00:41:34,123
Cricket teaches you many things.

613
00:41:34,243 --> 00:41:38,316
<i>Why lose out on fun?</i>

614
00:41:38,436 --> 00:41:42,163
<i>For fear of the others</i>

615
00:41:42,283 --> 00:41:46,099
<i>So what if the world disapproves?</i>

616
00:41:46,219 --> 00:41:48,415
<i>So be it</i>

617
00:41:48,540 --> 00:41:52,208
<i>Let us go a little wild</i>

618
00:41:52,328 --> 00:41:55,929
<i>Why be all serious now?</i>

619
