<i>We'll follow our hearts</i>

635
00:42:59,914 --> 00:43:01,563
Cheeka!

636
00:43:01,740 --> 00:43:03,190
Congrats.

637
00:43:03,310 --> 00:43:04,542
Hey!

638
00:43:07,304 --> 00:43:09,954
<i>What's there to fear?</i>

639
00:43:10,205 --> 00:43:11,808
I've never seen so many people.

640
00:43:12,540 --> 00:43:15,332
Man Singh, Kapil! Fantastic!

641
00:43:19,348 --> 00:43:21,673
- Hello, Wankhede sir.
- You won two matches!

642
00:43:22,414 --> 00:43:25,623
Mishra-ji, write a headline story
on the team.

643
00:43:25,748 --> 00:43:28,197
Sure, sir.
They've won two matches.

644
00:43:28,415 --> 00:43:31,663
Even if they had to return to
India tomorrow, it's OK.

645
00:43:33,748 --> 00:43:35,457
No one's going anywhere.

646
00:43:37,373 --> 00:43:39,373
You're booked to leave
on the 25th, right?

647
00:43:39,957 --> 00:43:41,040
Yes.

648
00:43:46,540 --> 00:43:50,602
What'll he do here till then?
Does Kapil want to watch the Finals?

649
00:43:51,165 --> 00:43:53,498
He intends to play in the Finals.

650
00:43:56,221 --> 00:43:57,582
I'm off.

651
00:44:00,873 --> 00:44:02,939
"Play in the Finals!"

652
00:44:03,582 --> 00:44:07,258
If we changed our tickets
from June 25th,

653
00:44:07,378 --> 00:44:09,803
must we pay a cancellation fee?

654
00:44:10,180 --> 00:44:12,873
Why would you care if we stayed
till the 25th?

655
00:44:12,998 --> 00:44:14,873
Just tell me about
the cancellation charges.

656
00:44:15,165 --> 00:44:18,290
How much? Really!

657
00:44:20,415 --> 00:44:22,893
Then don't change the booking.

658
00:44:24,181 --> 00:44:27,769
I was only asking to pass time.

659
00:44:28,858 --> 00:44:32,325
<i>And I can say this specially after
the fall of the first few wickets.</i>

660
00:44:41,727 --> 00:44:46,373
<i>In the other match today at Leeds,
West Indies beat Australia by 101 runs.</i>

661
00:44:46,582 --> 00:44:48,926
<i>An aggressive comeback after
their humiliating defeat to India.</i>

662
00:44:48,950 --> 00:44:50,279
Brother.

663
00:44:50,827 --> 00:44:52,294
Free dinner?

664
00:44:52,731 --> 00:44:53,800
Let's go.

665
00:44:55,165 --> 00:44:58,444
Ma'am, this is Kapil - Kapsy.

666
00:44:58,645 --> 00:45:00,416
Jimmy, our Vice-Captain.

667
00:45:00,631 --> 00:45:03,582
This is Mr and Mrs Natrajan
from Madurai.

668
00:45:03,846 --> 00:45:05,285
And their daughter, Kalyani.

669
00:45:06,658 --> 00:45:08,900
- She cooks very well, they say.
- That's nice.

670
00:45:12,048 --> 00:45:13,522
Shall we eat?

671
00:45:13,743 --> 00:45:15,391
It's delicious.

672
00:45:15,799 --> 00:45:18,165
The dosas are very good. Did you mix
the batter yourself?

673
00:45:18,285 --> 00:45:20,409
No, we get it from India.

674
00:45:20,964 --> 00:45:23,469
I've had five dosas already.

675
00:45:23,873 --> 00:45:26,789
Please don't count.
This is also like your house only.

676
00:45:26,957 --> 00:45:28,790
Kalyani enjoys cooking very much.

677
00:45:28,915 --> 00:45:30,133
Really nice.

678
00:45:31,709 --> 00:45:33,940
You've won two World Cup matches.

679
00:45:34,587 --> 00:45:36,489
Now you should marry.

680
00:45:45,981 --> 00:45:50,582
She says you've won two matches,

681
00:45:50,873 --> 00:45:52,868
so you should settle down.

682
00:45:54,545 --> 00:45:56,207
Cheeka is well settled.

683
00:45:56,332 --> 00:46:00,358
He got married to a lovely girl
in March.

684
00:46:06,060 --> 00:46:07,665
Didn't you tell them?

685
00:46:15,707 --> 00:46:17,383
Congratulations.

686
00:46:18,957 --> 00:46:20,535
Congratulations.

687
00:46:23,623 --> 00:46:24,879
Thank you.

688
00:46:33,832 --> 00:46:36,873
Did you have to tell them the truth
like Raja Harishchandra?

689
00:46:37,105 --> 00:46:39,207
A few more dosas would've been nice.

690
00:46:40,165 --> 00:46:43,582
- You rascal! Shall I tell Vidya?
- Kapsy!

691
00:46:44,207 --> 00:46:46,873
It's hard finding a vegetarian
South Indian family.

692
00:46:46,998 --> 00:46:50,123
You can find Punjabis everywhere.

693
00:46:51,498 --> 00:46:53,415
South Indian families are rare.

694
00:46:54,582 --> 00:46:59,957
A wife fills the heart.
Food fills the belly.

695
00:47:00,457 --> 00:47:02,353
You can't mix the two.

696
00:47:04,354 --> 00:47:06,222
The end of my dosas.

697
00:47:06,858 --> 00:47:10,373
He missed out on dessert,
that's why he's mad.

698
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:19,939
- Hello.
- How are you?

699
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:21,373
Simran...

700
00:47:21,498 --> 00:47:24,089
Sat Sri Akal.

701
00:47:24,373 --> 00:47:27,244
Say hello from me.

702
00:47:27,509 --> 00:47:28,582
She says hello.

703
00:47:28,707 --> 00:47:30,665
Hello-ji, sister-in-law.

704
00:47:30,849 --> 00:47:34,040
We won't tell you about Julie.

705
00:47:34,165 --> 00:47:36,540
Simran, I'll call you
from the lobby.

706
00:47:36,711 --> 00:47:39,248
- These idiots are teasing me.
- Wait. Who's Julie?

707
00:47:39,373 --> 00:47:41,915
There is no Julie.
He was just kidding.

708
00:47:42,040 --> 00:47:44,457
Let me call you from the lobby.
OK?

709
00:47:44,998 --> 00:47:48,332
Do you want my engagement
to be called off?

710
00:47:48,457 --> 00:47:51,462
Now she won't get Julie
out of her mind.

711
00:47:51,582 --> 00:47:55,566
Julie, I love you!

712
00:47:55,832 --> 00:47:57,373
Julie speaking.

713
00:47:57,707 --> 00:47:58,913
Lala-ji!

714
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:07,378
Who is Julie?
No, not Julie. I said July.

715
00:48:07,498 --> 00:48:10,087
Lala-ji, all the boys were sitting here.

716
00:48:10,207 --> 00:48:12,832
They want a short holiday
before going home.

717
00:48:12,957 --> 00:48:15,035
So, we'll be back in July not June.

718
00:48:15,288 --> 00:48:18,272
Everything's fine.
Do you want to talk to Jimmy?

719
00:48:19,415 --> 00:48:22,332
He isn't picking up?
One minute.

720
00:48:22,457 --> 00:48:23,707
Yes.

721
00:48:23,827 --> 00:48:26,381
He was right here.

722
00:48:28,498 --> 00:48:29,614
Jimmy!

723
00:48:29,790 --> 00:48:32,349
He must be somewhere in the hotel lobby.

724
00:48:33,140 --> 00:48:34,540
No, Lala-ji. No way.

725
00:48:34,660 --> 00:48:36,707
He never goes out at night.

726
00:48:36,827 --> 00:48:38,203
He's not here.

727
00:48:38,498 --> 00:48:41,529
He's gone to sleep, Lala-ji.

728
00:48:41,957 --> 00:48:43,332
Should I wake him up?

729
00:48:58,119 --> 00:49:00,150
Hello. Papa.

730
00:49:05,134 --> 00:49:06,649
What happened?

731
00:49:08,582 --> 00:49:10,373
Go, look for Jimmy.

732
00:49:10,539 --> 00:49:12,659
- Here he is.
- Jimpa, where were you?

733
00:49:13,082 --> 00:49:13,582
Why?

734
00:49:13,744 --> 00:49:16,962
- Lala-ji called.
- You should've said I was asleep.

735
00:49:17,140 --> 00:49:19,082
- He told me to wake you up.
- Then?

736
00:49:19,207 --> 00:49:21,441
Then I imitated your voice, but...

737
00:49:21,561 --> 00:49:22,561
But what?

738
00:49:22,660 --> 00:49:23,748
Lala-ji said:

739
00:49:23,873 --> 00:49:26,540
"Kirti, I'm not just Jimmy's father
but your father too."

740
00:49:26,660 --> 00:49:28,124
I hung up.

741
00:49:29,873 --> 00:49:30,962
Must be Lala-ji.

742
00:49:31,082 --> 00:49:33,873
I'm in trouble, thanks
to your free dosas.

743
00:49:33,998 --> 00:49:35,123
I warned you.

744
00:49:35,248 --> 00:49:36,915
Don't get trapped by free food.

745
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:39,430
- The dosas have cost you heavily.
- Yash, shut up.

746
00:49:45,248 --> 00:49:48,540
What else did Lala-ji say?

747
00:49:49,832 --> 00:49:52,803
- Just keep batting.
- He must've said something else.

748
00:49:54,055 --> 00:49:57,123
Watching you is hurting my muscles.

749
00:49:57,248 --> 00:49:58,663
Go easy!

750
00:50:00,665 --> 00:50:02,774
Look at this photographer!

751
00:50:03,135 --> 00:50:05,480
I'm the Man of the Match
and he's photographing you.

752
00:50:09,123 --> 00:50:10,707
It's simple, brother.

753
00:50:11,165 --> 00:50:13,457
Whoever pops the champagne cork
gets photographed.

754
00:50:13,832 --> 00:50:15,832
